Hello! I have started to read Harry Potter. FINALLY. Well, lately Ive become OBSSESSED. In fact, I start seeing things. (Also, I love Harry/Draco (Thanks to all of this, Kris! X3) Well, Im starting to see things.

Here are somethings:

  • *Walks into Belks ot some store of stupidness with Emily. Turn first corner and burst in to many thoughts* -Sight: A Stripped shirt, one Gryffindor colored one and a Slytherin colored one.- My thoughts were like, "Kris has been here, or to the head of the Belks company!! She has started to force  them to support Slash, mostly Harry/Draco!! O.O OMIGOD! Why didnt she tell me?! I could have helped!" Well, while I was thinking this, I was chuckling and at one point accidentally said something stupid. "Why didnt she tell me?!" Emily thankfully didnt hear me.
  • Second thing, I was at the pool today and I messed up Steven's hair, which then, looked like Harry's hair would be. Mad that his eyes were brown, not green, I started pulling on steven's hair saying in a mad way, "Why the Hell cant you look like Harry and have pretty green eyes!? Dammit, now I wanna read and I left my book so it didnt get wet...I might leave soon!" And, as always when I speak wayy faster than normal, my voice sounded English. Everytime I talk faster than I usually do, it happens.
  • Third, I have started to say Bloody *insert somethin here*. Well, usually when I was little, I Always used that word,  Ijust liked it, and back then, I hated everything English, I would like, go mad over it. I mostly hated Harry Potter too, I was like, "I love magic, but he is stupid, I mean, who would go chase someone who wants to kill you? If it were me, I would kill myself, then I wouldnt be afraid. Or, I would geta few friends, orce them to look like me, send them off everywhere and force this Voldy dude to just give up. Or would I kill him? I dont know. Its not nive to kill thou, maybe I could just use something to make him suffer until he begs to die. I dont know, but I just dont like it." My mom would look at me like, O.O What?  Yeah... No need to worry thou, I love it now
